                            <comment id="15037651" author="jinxing6042@126.com" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2015 10:48:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can reproduce this;&lt;br/&gt;
when we call consumer.seek(partition,offset), the offset must be bigger than the smallest LogSegment&apos;s baseOffset(beginning of the log) and smaller than log size(end of the log); &lt;br/&gt;
If not, we will get &quot;Fetch offset null is out of range&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
Setting offset to be negative is obvious invalid, maybe we can reject this request in the consumer side, without sending it to the broker;&lt;br/&gt;
Am I right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
